se.jguru.nazgul.core.quickstart.api.generator.parser

Class SingleBracketPomTokenParserFactory.PrefixEnricher

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.jguru.nazgul.core.quickstart.api.generator.parser.SingleBracketPomTokenParserFactory.PrefixEnricher
  • Enclosing class:
    SingleBracketPomTokenParserFactory

    public static class SingleBracketPomTokenParserFactory.PrefixEnricher
extends Object
    BuilderStep which adds the prefix of Maven GroupIDs for a relative path within a directory. A "groupIdPrefix" is normally identical to a reverse DNS of the project's organisation, similar to se.jguru or org.acme. Note that the groupIdPrefix should not include the project name (i.e. project.getName()), as it will be automatically appended by this builder. Given a SoftwareComponent with the relative path services/finance, the groupIdPrefix se.jguru and the project name foo, the full groupId of the finance service SoftwareComponent can be constructed as se.jguru.foo.services.finance. This, in turn, implies that the API project in the finance SoftwareComponent will retrieve the groupId se.jguru.foo.services.finance.api.

        public SingleBracketPomTokenParserFactory.SuffixEnricher withProjectGroupIdPrefix(String projectGroupIdPrefix)
        Adds prefix which should be prepended to the relative path to generate a groupId for the current project. A "projectGroupIdPrefix" is normally identical to a reverse DNS of the project's organisation, similar to se.jguru or org.acme. Note that the groupIdPrefix should not include the project name (i.e. project.getName()), as it will be automatically appended by this builder.
        Parameters:
        projectGroupIdPrefix - A non-null prefix string added to the relative path to generate a groupId for the current project. Empty values are permitted, but null are not. Normally identical to a reverse DNS of the project's organisation, similar to se.jguru or org.acme. Note that the groupIdPrefix should not include the project name (i.e. project.getName()), as it will be automatically appended by this builder.

        protected boolean isProjectNameAddedToDirectories()
        Returns:
        true if this BuilderStep should add prefixes with the Project's name to local project directory names. This means that SoftwareComponent directories should be given names on the form foo-finance-api instead of finance-api, given that the project's name is foo and the SoftwareComponent's finance.
